    "attributes": {
        "action": "Government to Give More Power to SFO to Investigate financial institutions",
        "additional_details": "The SFO to be given unlimited powers to investigate/access all records from all parties:\r\n \r\nInsurance Companies/Building Societies/Banks\r\nExperts such as Land/Building Surveyors & Engineers\r\nIndependent Industry Complaint Bodies\r\n \r\nThis would better enable the SFO to investigate complaints, and take appropriate action.",
        "background": "The Financial Ombudsman have no powers to investigate complex complaints involving more than one party, particularly when insurance claims have failed due to incorrect input by several parties. A new law is vital to enable the Serious Fraud Office to investigate complaints of this type.",
